# 🕹️ GridVerse: A Multiplayer Tile-Based Chat Game

**GridVerse** is a real-time multiplayer tile-based game that enables players to move across a 2D map, interact with the environment, and engage in retro-style proximity chat when adjacent to each other.

> Built using **React**, **Tailwind CSS**, and **Go** with **WebSockets** for real-time communication and **ScyllaDB** for persistent data storage.

---

## 🚀 Features

- 👥 Real-time multiplayer movement
- 🧱 2D tile-based map rendering
- 🏠 House tiles and collision detection
- 📡 Proximity-based chat (opens when players are adjacent)
- 🎮 Smooth player animations with retro-style chat UI
- 🔐 Login/Signup system
- ⚙️ Backend built with Go, using WebSockets for live updates

---

## 🛠️ Tech Stack

**Frontend:**
- React
- Tailwind CSS
- WebSockets (client)
- Vite (or Create React App)

**Backend:**
- Go (Golang)
- Gorilla Mux for routing
- WebSockets (server-side)
- ScyllaDB (NoSQL) for user and room data

